pect to the reference model, a\nCR-regulated IMF implies shorter star formation histories and higher peaks of\nstar formation for objects more massive than $10^{10.5} M_\\odot$. However, we\nalso show that it is difficult to unveil this behaviour from observations, as\nthe key physical quantities are typically derived assuming a universal IMF.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Jan 2018 19:00:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-14"}
