.15, fabricated on 200-mm wafers by co-sputtering. We demonstrate that the\nelectron transport mechanism in Si$_{1-x}$Nb$_x$ barriers at x < 0.08 is\ninelastic resonant tunneling via chains of multiple localized states. At larger\nx, their Josephson characteristics are strongly dependent on x and residual\nstress in Nb electrodes, and in general are inferior to AlO$_x$ tunnel\nbarriers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Jan 2018 19:42:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-02"}
