his\nemission matches the expectations of a Gaussian structured relativistic jet,\nwhich would have launched a high luminosity short GRB to an aligned observer.\nHowever, other jet structure or cocoon models can also match current data - the\nfuture evolution of the afterglow will directly distinguish the origin of the\nemission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Jan 2018 20:09:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Jan 2018 13:54:28 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 19 Sep 2018 10:17:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-20"}
